The paper deals with the efficient computation of representative sets for families of sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The paper also mentions applications in dynamic programming algorithms and graph theory, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
